	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />My understanding of the reason for this extra cycle is that the 6502 has a single general-purpose 8-bit adder that it reuses for various tasks, including indexed absolute addressing mode. On the first cycle it adds X to the low byte of the target address. If a carry is generated, it needs to take an extra cycle to add one to the high byte. This also explains why the low byte of addresses is stored first.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
